We might need to cool it down for 10 minutes and start again.
我们可能需要让它冷却10分钟，然后再重新开始。

163
00:07:57,760 --> 00:08:00,800
I'll call IT support to come over right now.
我现在就叫IT支持过来。

164
00:08:00,800 --> 00:08:06,040
Okay guys, unfortunately technical problems do crop up from time to time, don't they?
好了各位，不幸的是，技术问题时不时就会冒出来，对吧？

165
00:08:06,040 --> 00:08:07,520
But it's not a huge problem.
但这也不是什么大问题。

166
00:08:07,520 --> 00:08:11,300
In the meantime, while the IT guys get to work on that, I can talk a little bit more
与此同时，在IT人员处理这个问题的时候，我可以再多讲一点

167
00:08:11,300 --> 00:08:20,720
about the advertising concept and what we are looking to achieve overall with this campaign.
关于广告概念以及我们这次活动想要达成的整体目标。

168
00:08:20,720 --> 00:08:26,640
Alright we're back so now let's take a look at some phrases on Fluency Builder.
好了，我们回来了，现在来看看Fluency Builder上的一些短语。

169
00:08:26,640 --> 00:08:28,360
Fluency Builder.
Fluency Builder。

170
00:08:28,360 --> 00:08:33,640
So this first phrase we have is very important, especially when we're using video or a projector
所以这第一个短语非常重要，尤其是当我们在演示中使用视频或投影仪时

171
00:08:33,640 --> 00:08:34,640
in a presentation.
在演示中。

172
00:08:34,640 --> 00:08:37,520
We say, let's dim the lights.
我们会说，让我们把灯光调暗。

173
00:08:37,520 --> 00:08:38,520
That's right.
没错。

174
00:08:38,520 --> 00:08:40,280
So we have the verb to dim.
所以我们有动词“调暗”。

175
00:08:40,280 --> 00:08:44,240
So to dim something is to make it darker.
所以调暗某物就是让它变得更暗。

176
00:08:44,240 --> 00:08:46,400
But not turn it off completely.
但不是完全关掉。

177
00:08:46,400 --> 00:08:47,400
No.
不是。

178
00:08:47,400 --> 00:08:51,200
It means maybe to lower the lights.
它意味着可能降低灯光亮度。

179
00:08:51,200 --> 00:08:55,360
We could actually see this on a computer also when the screen is very, very bright.
我们在电脑上也能看到这种情况，当屏幕非常亮的时候。

180
00:08:55,360 --> 00:08:57,520
We say, oh it's too bright.
我们会说，哦，太亮了。

181
00:08:57,520 --> 00:08:59,880
I need you to dim it a little.
我需要你把它调暗一点。

182
00:08:59,880 --> 00:09:01,360
Make it a little bit darker.
让它暗一点。

183
00:09:01,360 --> 00:09:02,360
Okay.
好的。

184
00:09:02,360 --> 00:09:07,160
So you can use this verb to dim to make it a little bit darker or to make it lower in
所以你可以用这个动词“调暗”来让它变暗一点或降低

185
00:09:07,160 --> 00:09:08,400
intensity.
强度。

186
00:09:08,400 --> 00:09:09,400
That's right.
没错。

187
00:09:09,400 --> 00:09:10,400
Dim the color, dim the lights.
调暗颜色，调暗灯光。

188
00:09:10,400 --> 00:09:12,160
Alright, very good.
好的，非常好。

189
00:09:12,160 --> 00:09:16,920
Now Mr. Ford when he was talking about the advert, he said, well it's new and it's not
现在福特先生谈到广告时，他说，嗯，这是新的，而且还没有

190
00:09:16,920 --> 00:09:18,560
ready yet completely.
完全准备好。

191
00:09:18,560 --> 00:09:22,240
So it might seem a bit rough around the edges.
所以它可能看起来有点粗糙。

192
00:09:22,240 --> 00:09:23,240
Okay.
好的。

193
00:09:23,240 --> 00:09:28,240
This is a very, very popular phrase that means that something is incomplete.
这是一个非常非常流行的短语，意思是某物还不完整。

194
00:09:28,240 --> 00:09:29,600
Maybe it's not perfect yet.
可能还不完美。

195
00:09:29,600 --> 00:09:30,600
It needs some work.
还需要一些改进。

196
00:09:30,600 --> 00:09:31,600
Okay.
好的。

197
00:09:31,600 --> 00:09:36,820
So if maybe you're designing a new website and it's maybe 50% done.
所以如果你在设计一个新网站，可能完成了50%。

198
00:09:36,820 --> 00:09:41,340
So you say the website is almost finished, but it's still rough around the edges.
你会说网站差不多完成了，但还是有点粗糙。

199
00:09:41,340 --> 00:09:43,960
We need to make some changes to fix it.
我们需要做一些修改来完善它。

200
00:09:43,960 --> 00:09:44,960
That's right.
没错。

201
00:09:44,960 --> 00:09:50,200
Rough around the edges is a phrase that is the opposite of the word polished.
“粗糙”这个短语是“精致”的反义词。

202
00:09:50,200 --> 00:09:53,280
Something is polished if it's perfect and ready to go.
如果某物是精致的，那就意味着它完美无缺，可以用了。

203
00:09:53,280 --> 00:09:54,280
Okay.
好的。

204
00:09:54,280 --> 00:10:00,640
And well, when the technical problem started, Mr. Ford was apologizing and said, hey, look,
嗯，当技术问题出现时，福特先生道歉说，嘿，听着，

205
00:10:00,640 --> 00:10:01,760
I'm sorry.
对不起。

206
00:10:01,760 --> 00:10:05,480
And he also used this interesting phrase, bear with me.
他还用了一个有趣的短语，“请耐心等待”。

207
00:10:05,480 --> 00:10:06,480
Bear with me a second.
请稍等一下。

208
00:10:06,480 --> 00:10:07,480
Okay.
好的。

209
00:10:07,480 --> 00:10:09,600
So this is interesting because it's not the animal, the bear.
这很有趣，因为它不是指动物熊。

210
00:10:09,600 --> 00:10:10,600
Right, right.
对，对。

211
00:10:10,600 --> 00:10:11,600
This is different.
这是不同的。

212
00:10:11,600 --> 00:10:16,160
It's more like, excuse me, please be patient.
它更像是，对不起，请耐心点。

213
00:10:16,160 --> 00:10:18,400
I have to do something and you have to wait.
我得做点事，你得等一下。

214
00:10:18,400 --> 00:10:22,960
So this is a very, very polite way of asking some people or some person to wait for you.
所以这是一种非常非常礼貌的方式，请求别人或某人等你。

215
00:10:22,960 --> 00:10:23,960
To tolerate.
容忍。

216
00:10:23,960 --> 00:10:24,960
Yes.
是的。

217
00:10:24,960 --> 00:10:29,760
So both the animal bear and to bear with me are spelled the same way.
所以动物熊和“请耐心等待”的拼写是一样的。

218
00:10:29,760 --> 00:10:32,520
It looks exactly like the animal, but we're not talking about the animal.
它看起来完全像动物，但我们不是在说动物。

219
00:10:32,520 --> 00:10:38,000
No, we're asking someone to tolerate something that's annoying or frustrating.
不，我们是在请求某人容忍一些烦人或令人沮丧的事情。

220
00:10:38,000 --> 00:10:39,000
Okay.
好的。

221
00:10:39,000 --> 00:10:42,960
For example, I'm trying to show you a file on my computer, Marco.
例如，Marco，我正想给你看我电脑上的一个文件。

222
00:10:42,960 --> 00:10:44,160
My computer's not working.
我的电脑不工作了。

223
00:10:44,160 --> 00:10:45,920
I say, please bear with me a second.
我会说，请稍等一下。

224
00:10:45,920 --> 00:10:47,640
I have to reboot my computer.
我得重启电脑。

225
00:10:47,640 --> 00:10:49,200
I have to wait here.
我得在这儿等着。

226
00:10:49,200 --> 00:10:50,200
Okay.
好的。

227
00:10:50,200 --> 00:10:51,200
Very good.
非常好。

228
00:10:51,200 --> 00:10:55,400
Now, towards the end of the dialogue, when we talked about to crop up, the second part
现在，在对话快结束时，当我们谈到“突然出现”时，第二部分

229
00:10:55,400 --> 00:11:02,440
of that, Mr. Ford said, unfortunately, technical problems do crop up from time to time.
福特先生说，不幸的是，技术问题时不时就会冒出来。

230
00:11:02,440 --> 00:11:05,200
So we already discussed cropped up.
我们已经讨论过“突然出现”了。

231
00:11:05,200 --> 00:11:06,720
What is time to time?
“时不时”是什么意思？

232
00:11:06,720 --> 00:11:07,720
From time to time.
时不时。

233
00:11:07,720 --> 00:11:08,720
Okay.
好的。

234
00:11:08,720 --> 00:11:12,920
So that's a set phrase because we said already that you could also say sometimes.
这是一个固定短语，因为我们已经说过你也可以说“有时”。

235
00:11:12,920 --> 00:11:18,860
So from time to time means every once in a while or occasionally.
所以“时不时”意思是偶尔或间或。

236
00:11:18,860 --> 00:11:21,160
So it's an adverbial phrase.
所以它是一个副词短语。

237
00:11:21,160 --> 00:11:26,260
It's a way of telling people how often something happens, but in this case, it's not very common.
这是一种告诉人们某事发生频率的方式，但在这里，它不是很常见。

238
00:11:26,260 --> 00:11:30,160
So for example, you can say, I like to go to the movies from time to time.
例如，你可以说，我时不时喜欢去看电影。

239
00:11:30,160 --> 00:11:31,160
That's right.
没错。

240
00:11:31,160 --> 00:11:34,360
So maybe once or twice a month, you like to go to the movies.
所以可能一个月一两次，你喜欢去看电影。

241
00:11:34,360 --> 00:11:36,680
But what if I come to work every day?
但如果我每天都来上班呢？

242
00:11:36,680 --> 00:11:38,280
Do I come to work from time to time?
我是不是偶尔来上班？

243
00:11:38,280 --> 00:11:39,280
No.
不。

244
00:11:39,280 --> 00:11:40,280
Right.
对。

245
00:11:40,280 --> 00:11:41,280
Okay.
好的。

246
00:11:41,280 --> 00:11:44,360
So from time to time is rarely or occasionally, not very often.
所以“from time to time”意思是很少或偶尔，不经常。

247
00:11:44,360 --> 00:11:45,360
Exactly.
没错。

248
00:11:45,360 --> 00:11:46,360
All right.
好了。

249
00:11:46,360 --> 00:11:47,360
Very good.
非常好。

250
00:11:47,360 --> 00:11:52,840
